<br>
Since non level 60s still have new things to look forward to as they level there appears to be a desire for each class to get many new level 60 spells (some of which replace other level 60 spells already in possession).<br>
<br>
What I would like to see in PoP (more in order of current annoyance than desire):<br>
<br>
<br>
1. New animations (yeah, they say it isn't going to happen, but they still suck).<br>
<br>
2. LEG GEOMETRY for armor.  It isn't there.  Plate looks like pantyhose.<br>
<br>
3. New interface DONE (yeah, was slated for last Dec...)<br>
<br>
4. Bazaar function implemented (same)<br>
<br>
5. IN GAME diaries.  You could click on any block of text (each single say, etc, would be a block) and drag them to your diary to keep them for use in game.  Stored entirely on your system, and with text not taking much room should NOT be a problem.<br>
<br>
6. Click-the-keyword quests.  Hey, the dwarf says, &quot;I lost my (sister).&quot;  If you are going to give such hints to quests you may as well have people click on it rather than say &quot;which sister, where is your sister, tell me about your sister, DAMN YOU LITTLE FRIGGIN DWARF TELL ME WHERE YOU SISTER IS SO I CAN HUNT HER DOWN!!!&quot;  Now, I have NO problem with NON keyword quests at all.  In fact I prefer them, but if they are in take the last step.<br>
<br>
7. Revise graphics engine.  It is horribly inefficient still.  Sure, the culling part seems to work now, but how it renders what it does still seems to be overly taxing for what you get out of it.<br>
<br>
8. LOTS of interesting deity specific quests.  Yes, sorry there ARE going to be people who whine if God A's sword is 46/44 with 15 ac and 100pt DD, and God B's sword is 47/45 with 10 ac and 105 pt dd.  ACCEPT that people will wine if they can't min/max 100%.<br>
<br>
9. FEW, if any irreparable factions (or insanely hard to repare factions).  At the higher levels this is a game based on HR skills and tactics.  It doesn't help to devise situations where some of the best items in the game come from creatures like Tunare and encourage tactics like, &quot;PoG lovers /q NOW&quot; when fighting them.  The current coldain/zek/rif/cov factions are nice.  Yes, you fight them you are hurt, but all are reparable in a couple dozen hours at most.  I would have *no* problem with making faction requirements to *equip* items.  Would limit the benefit of faction jumping, as long as factions were reparable.  (e.g. no you are not entitled to be able to wear rallos zek BP and quellious legs at the same time as they are opposed factions).  Just an idead, doubt it will happen.<br>
